  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The filling thickens in the oven as the cherry juices heat and activate the cornflour; but it only sets fully as the pie cools. Cutting a hot cherry pie gives a liquid filling. Rest the pie for at least 20 minutes before cutting for a filling that holds its shape. The lattice allows the filling to bubble up visibly and lets steam escape, which prevents a soggy bottom crust."
          }
        ]
      },
